.TH PACSAT-UPLOAD 1 "December 27, 2025" "1.0.0" "PACSAT Revival Project"
.SH NAME
pacsat-upload \- Upload files to PACSAT ground station via REST API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B curl
\-X POST http://localhost:8000/upload
.br
\-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"
.br
\-F "file=@/path/to/file"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pacsat-upload
is a command-line example for uploading files to the PACSAT ground station using the REST API.
The ground station accepts files via multipart/form-data and generates authentic PACSAT File Headers (PFH).
Uploaded files are stored in the conventional subdirectory hierarchy and become available for broadcast.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-X POST
Use HTTP POST method
.TP
.B \-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"
JWT authentication token obtained from /token endpoint
.TP
.B \-F "file=@/path/to/file"
Local file to upload (multiple \-F for batch)
.TP
.B \-F "file=@file1" \-F "file=@file2"
Batch upload (use /upload/batch endpoint)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Single file upload
    curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/upload" \\
         -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \\
         -F "file=@news.txt"
.TP
Batch upload
    curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/upload/batch" \\
         -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \\
         -F "file=@file1.txt" \\
         -F "file=@file2.bin"
.SH RESPONSE
On success, returns JSON with file_num, filename (8.3 format), size, and upload time.
.SH AUTHENTICATION
First obtain token:
    curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/token" \\
         -d "username=youruser&password=yourpass"
